Coleophora ravillella is a moth of the family Coleophoridae. It is found in France, Spain and Italy.
The larvae feed on Onobrychis saxatilis and Onobrychis viciifolia. They create a bivalved lobe case or a very untidy composite leaf case of 7â€“9 mm long. It is made up of 4-5 withered leaflets. The mouth opening is shifted laterally.